{"TopicId":173478,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"minThrust handling request","CreatedByName":"Psycho_zs","CreatedById":137644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T11:09:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Psycho_zs","CreatedById":137644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T11:09:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello everyone!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince Squad hasn\u0027t yet addressed the problem with minThrust handling (engines with minThrust \u0026gt; 0\u00A0 can not be shut down by throttle, complex bug report is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/15826\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E) ,\u00A0 I would like to request the \u003Cstrong\u003Esimplest possible\u003C/strong\u003E mod solution that does just that without affecting anything else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA good starting point would be\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B45cFsYMm_H-RUp3WDBqRkhuclk\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThrottleControlledShutdown\u003C/a\u003E plugin by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172906-nottherealrms/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022172906\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/172906-nottherealrms/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NotTheRealRMS\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0 which dynamically sets engine\u0027s minThrust to 0 when ship\u0027s throttle is 0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe someone would be kind enough to refurbish and clean this thing up, (i.e. \u0027foreach\u0027 are bad as far as I heard). Or maybe there is a better way to solve the problem altogether.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: this plugin works in 1.4.2. Although\u00A0 it sometimes lags behind throttle and other ships coming into physics bubble may have their engines unaffected and therefore ignited.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-06T17:38:50Z\u0022 title=\u002204/06/2018 05:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 6, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Psycho_zs\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T08:46:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat engines have \u0026gt;0 min thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch should cover it.\u00A0 I literally just looked up how to write a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch for another item, and it seems fairly simple to write one that will set all your engines to have 0 min thrust, or a little longer if you want to do specific ones.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/sarbian/ModuleManager/wiki/Module-Manager-Handbook\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/sarbian/ModuleManager/wiki/Module-Manager-Handbook\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Psycho_zs","CreatedById":137644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T08:53:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522918006\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat engines have \u0026gt;0 min thrust?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModded. Like by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169352-131-throttle-limit-extended/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=3268331\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E kind of patch. You missed the point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T09:13:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345506\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522918426\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137644\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Psycho_zs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Psycho_zs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou missed the point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really, I just went with what was provided.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345506\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522918426\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137644\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Psycho_zs\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Psycho_zs said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nModded. Like by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169352-131-throttle-limit-extended/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=3268331\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethis\u003C/a\u003E kind of patch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving read that thread, it seems it needs be fixed within that mod, or any mod that does this.\u00A0\u00A0 Adding a mod to fix a mod doesn\u0027t seem right, when the authors are active.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Psycho_zs","CreatedById":137644,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T09:18:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345521\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522919593\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaving read that thread, it seems it needs be fixed within that mod, or any mod that does this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat mod is irrelevant. The point is not to set minThrust to 0 (like by not applying the patch). The point is to shut down engines that have minThrust \u0026gt; 0. One way to do it is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edynamically\u003C/strong\u003E set minThrust to 0 when ship\u0027s throttle is 0 and revert the value when throttle is not 0. This can not be done by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}